{"entry_type":"decision","summary":"Add per-user send queue to NotificationService to guarantee notification delivery order","detail":"Added a per-user promise chain (sendQueues Map) in NotificationService. Each send() call chains onto the previous promise for the same queue key, ensuring sequential delivery per user. The queue key uses metadata.userId when available, falling back to params.recipient, so notifications for the same user are serialized even when the recipient field differs across notification types (e.g., email address vs user ID). The actual send logic was extracted to a private deliverNotification() method called within the chain. This is minimal — no new dependencies, no architectural changes, preserves the existing EventBus + adapter pattern.","tags":["implementation"],"scope":"src/services/notification.service.ts","agent_id":"agent-10","id":"01KMYBNXTSXQ3J60EN1NDWBQ1W","timestamp":"2026-03-30T03:12:59.225Z"}
